* [[Minas Tirith (Beleriand)|Minas Tirith]] upon [[Tol Sirion]] is captured by [[Sauron]], who makes the island his residence; it becames renamed [[Tol-in-Gaurhoth]], "''Isle of Werewolves''". Although defeated, [[Orodreth]] is saved by [[Celegorm]] and [[Curufin]]; they escape to [[Nargothrond]] together.<ref>{{S|18}}</ref><ref>{{LR|AB}}, entry for the year '257 [457]', p. 133</ref>

==Other versions of the legendarium==
According to ''[[The Grey Annals]]'', the capture of Minas Tirith by Sauron took place in {{FA|455}}, even before [[Fingolfin]] was slain in his [[Fall of Fingolfin|last stand]] against [[Morgoth]].<ref>{{GA|153-4}}</ref> However, [[Christopher Tolkien]] eventually did not include this change in the chronology into the [[The Silmarillion|published ''Silmarillion'']], preferring an earlier version from ''[[The Later Annals of Beleriand]].

